description: While I was scanning up and down the power pole from my previous observation, I saw some movement, and after a while, a female came out of one of the holes, looking around. I kept low, took plenty of cute pictures, and waited. Nine minutes later, she was visited by a male, for what looked like a shift handover. The female flew away, and the male crawled into the hole, and appeared again, looking. Four minutes later, another male showed up, looked into the hole, and then flew off again. I waited a bit longer, but the male inside the hole must have settled in and didn't come out again. The story continued two days later, https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/13773761.

When I came back from my hike, I spent a bit more time observing the action at this power pole -- my next observation.
